name: scljet-sql-where-expr
description: SclJet SQL expressions in WHERE — arithmetic on both sides, column-to-column, literal LHS, over a join; matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL expressions in WHERE

Either side of a `WHERE` comparison may be a scalar expression, not just `column op literal`:
`salary * 2 > 400`, `salary > cost * 2`, column-to-column (`salary > cost`), a literal on the left
(`250 >= salary`), and expressions composed with `AND`/`OR`. It also works across a join
(`emp.salary > dept.base * 2`). Every result is byte-identical to reference sqlite3 running the same
SQL on the same file (verified out-of-band); locked here across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows, executeMutation](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def apply(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): ByteSlice =
  executeMutation(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) =>
      println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
      db
    case Right(next) => next

def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "emp", "CREATE TABLE emp(id INTEGER, name TEXT, salary INTEGER, cost INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("ann"), SqlInteger(100L), SqlInteger(50L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob"), SqlInteger(250L), SqlInteger(200L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("cat"), SqlInteger(300L), SqlInteger(100L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("dan"), SqlInteger(150L), SqlInteger(150L)),
       List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("eve"), SqlInteger(260L), SqlInteger(130L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db0) =>
    val db1 = apply(db0, "CREATE TABLE dept(did INTEGER, base INTEGER)")
    val db2 = apply(db1, "INSERT INTO dept VALUES (1,60),(3,100),(5,130)")
    show(db2, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE salary * 2 > 400")
    show(db2, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE salary > cost * 2")
    show(db2, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE salary > cost")
    show(db2, "SELECT id, salary - cost FROM emp WHERE salary - cost > 100")
    show(db2, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE salary + cost >= 400 AND salary < 300")
    show(db2, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE salary / 100 = 2")
    show(db2, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE 250 >= salary")
    show(db2, "SELECT emp.id FROM emp JOIN dept ON emp.id = dept.did WHERE emp.salary > dept.base * 2")
```
